Police believe far-right extremists are responsible for the desecration of a Muslim cemetery in Austria, which occurred on the same weekend that far-right parties made significant gains in the national parliamentary elections.
More than 90 graves were badly damaged in the Trauni cemetery near Linz, sometime between Friday night and this morning, in what police believe to be an organized action.
