The setting and the plot are still unknown to him, but Mario Vargas Llosa is working on a new novel, the main character of which is an Irish nationalist, Roger Casemant, who has lived for twenty years in the Congo and has also travelled the Amazon.
The writer, who is up for the Nobel Prize in Literature, admitted at the Hay Festival in Segovia yesterday that his current work is "a total daredevil" and that "all indications are that it should not be written".
