As soon as the Liberal Party assembly was over, Jean Charest was already on his way to Jean-Talon, Quebec, yesterday, where the new health minister, Yves Bolduc (left), is seeking to win the midterm elections today.
'Reclaiming our last great northern border': this ambitious long-term goal was set by Jean Charest at yesterday's meeting of the Quebec Liberal Party in Lévis.
During his lecture, behind the back of the stage, a series of images similar to "Moulin à images" were projected.
