The fourth pillar of the "Northern Plan" is the "vision" of the Prime Minister for the future of Québec, which is embodied in a "new economic area", which includes a labour agreement with France, an agreement between Canada and Europe and several agreements with Ontario.
The opening up to the North (i.e. the northern area starting at the 49th parallel) has been a frequent topic in the Prime Minister's speeches in recent times, but he has never given a lecture on this subject.
The Head of State, however, only explained why he considered the North to be "a treasure trove of enormous possibilities", without mentioning the time factor, the amount of investment, or the specific priority of future projects.
