"This is ours, our future!" he added, after taking a stage break to gaze at the giant map behind him.
The North, which covers 70% of Quebec, includes a part of Labrador that Quebec has always claimed for itself, the head of government said at a press conference.
"This is our historic resolution, which has been endorsed by all governments.
There is a line that has been a long time without agreement and if the opportunity arises, I will reaffirm the same position on behalf of the government", he said.
On the other hand, "we must rethink our approach to the North in the light of climate change", he said, referring to the north-western passage that opens up every year as the polar ice melts.
