Plus, the bill was for the food, and the restaurant hasn't been open for a while.
The enthusiastic account creators did not investigate the fact that the travel agency in Budapest, which they looked at, only organised foreign trips, so they marked travel in Hungary as a service on the cash payment account, which was also not in line with the company's invoice issuing practice.
Moreover, as the investigation revealed, the document included VAT, whereas the travel activity to countries outside the European Union was exempt from VAT.
Among other things, the VAT rate was incorrect in the four documents issued by Hotel Révfülöp Kft. to Jobb Jövőért, because the company's service was not charged with the indicated 25 percent VAT, but with 15 percent VAT, and the hotel employees only issued a machine-made invoice, while the manufactured invoice was hand-made.
