Also, because of the irregularities - the wrong invoice format, the wrong stamp - it turned out that the invoices for the Together for the Third Millennium Foundation, the 21st Century Cultural Association and the Safe Point were fake.
As in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Sportkamp in Kunfeherto, whose representatives denied that they had issued the invoices.
The forgers did not even pay attention to the fact that HIB Kft. in Ariegyháza was being liquidated at the time (2001), when the group of the Association for the Young City was dining there, which is why the liquidator of the company - as far as we know - denied that he had drawn up the paper.
They deliberately set off
